description:
&lt;p&gt;The Sussex Voices Clinic (SVC) offers packages of psychologically-informed interventions to patients distressed by hearing voices, irrespective of diagnosis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We wish to appoint a Research Assistant to support the delivery of our interventions across our services for adults and young people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will be based within clinical services in West Sussex and be responsible for assessing patients and supporting them to engage with the interventions. SVC is also a research service, so opportunities will exist to be involved with the delivery of high-quality research studies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would welcome applications from motivated and organised psychology graduates who wish to develop their clinical and research skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sussex Partnership is one of the most research active Mental Health Trusts in England. The successful applicants will be supported by a large and expanding Research &amp; Development Department that is committed to the design, delivery and translation of high quality research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Anna-Marie Jones&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title R&amp;D Improvement Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address Anna-Marie.Jones@sussexpartnership.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 07738 757 554&lt;/p&gt;
